7:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Make (Integromat) and Parabola share a solid foundation of core features including Visual Builder, Api Connections, Scheduling, Conditional Logic. Where Make (Integromat) pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Code Support and Ai Actions, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on these capabilities. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Make (Integromat) holds an overall score of 9/10 and an ease of use score of 7/10, while Parabola scores 7/10 overall and 8/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
8:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, both Make (Integromat) and Parabola offer flexible pricing models. Both platforms offer free plans, which is great for testing before committing. Make (Integromat)'s free tier and Parabola's free tier each have their own limitations, so it is worth evaluating both to see which free offering better matches your initial needs."}]]}]
